# Senior Guide (Grades 6-13) ğŸ“š

Welcome to the ELEVATE Student Portal. This guide covers managing your academic tasks, submissions, and performance tracking.

## 1. Getting Started

### Dashboard Tour
- **Metrics:** Your current course progress and attendance stats.
- **Deadlines Widget:** Upcoming submissions due in the next 3 days.
- **Active Courses:** Quick links to your enrolled subjects.

## 2. Assignments & Quizzes

Navigate to **"Assignments"** to view your workload.

### Submitting a PDF/File
1. Find the assignment in the list.
2. Click **"Submit PDF"**.
3. **Upload Dialog:**
   - Click "Select File".
   - Choose your PDF (Max 10MB).
   - Click **"Submit Assignment"**.
4. Status will change to **"Pending Review"**.

### Taking an Online Quiz (MCQ)
1. Look for assignments marked **"Quiz"**.
2. Click **"Take Quiz"**.
3. **Quiz Interface:**
   - Read questions carefully.
   - Select the best answer.
   - Click **"Submit Quiz"** when done.
4. **Instant Results:** You will see your score (e.g., 18/20) immediately!

## 3. Tracking Performance

Navigate to **"Performance"** (or Grades).

- **Grade Book:** See scores for all past assignments.
- **Progress Bars:** Visual tracking of subject completion.
- **Attendance:** Check if you were marked present/absent.

## 4. Class Schedule

Navigate to **"Schedule"** to see your personalized timetable.
- **Blue events:** Regular classes
- **Red events:** Exams
- **Green events:** Assignment deadlines

## 5. Payments

Navigate to **"Payments"** to check your fee status.
